   "source": [
    "from prose import blocks\n",
    "from prose.tutorials import example_image\n",
    "\n",
    "# our example image\n",
    "image = example_image()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Creating and applying the Trim block\n",
    "trim = blocks.Trim(trim=100)\n",
    "trimmed_image = trim(image)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "34afd44c-ca96-433e-9f89-782eebdae6bb",

   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0.0, 1.0, 'trimmed image')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 864x288 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 4))\n",
    "\n",
    "ax1 = plt.subplot(121)\n",
    "image.show(ax=ax1)\n",
    "trim.draw_cutout(image)\n",
    "plt.axis(\"off\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"original image (white = cutout)\", loc=\"left\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax2 = plt.subplot(122)\n",
    "trimmed_image.show(ax=ax2)\n",
    "plt.axis(\"off\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"trimmed image\", loc=\"left\")"
   ]
  },
